# Lexer Diagrams

I've used some made-up character classes in the diagrams.

> [:id0:] === [A-Za-z_!$%&*/<=>?@^|~]
> [:id:] === [:id0:0-9+-]
>
> [:bin:] === [01]
> [:oct:] === [:0-7:]
> [:hex:] === [0-9A-Fa-f]

To edit a diagram, use https://cascii.com.
Click the "Base64 I/O" button along the top and paste in the base64 for the given diagram.
